Class DelegatingPrintStream

  • Object
    • OutputStream
      • FilterOutputStream
        • PrintStream
          • DelegatingPrintStream
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, Flushable, Appendable, AutoCloseable

    public class DelegatingPrintStream
extends PrintStream
    A derivative of PrintStream which delegates to an internally stored reference to a "real" PrintStream which can be changed. Can be used to create a substitute for System.out or System.err that ConsoleTester getOutput methods can redirect to string buffers dfr sending output to and later switch back to the original version to the original versions as they do System.out and System.err.

    Useful for passing a PrintStream class instance or argument with a method reference that requires one.

    Author:
    John Armstrong
